    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>By Mr. GRAVES of Missouri:H.R. 228.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article 1; Section 8; Necessary and Proper ClauseCongress created the SNAP program, formerly known as foodstamps, to provide a social safety net for the leastfortunate in our society. However, that social safety net andthe tax payers who support it are being defrauded to the tuneof millions of dollars a year. Therefore, it is bothnecessary and proper to protect the taxpayers' money throughpolicies which aim to prevent fraud within the SNAP program.[Page H85]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
    <amendments />
